modules.description: Provides functions for reading from and writing to key/value stores, with support for string values and Lwt-based I/O. Works with key/value pairs where keys are strings and values are either strings or arbitrary data. Used in MirageOS applications to interact with persistent or in-memory storage backends.

Provides operations to interact with a key-value store, including checking existence, retrieving values, listing dictionary entries, and obtaining modification times and digests. Works with keys of type `Mirage_kv.Key.t` and values represented as strings. Supports use cases like checking if a key maps to a value or dictionary, fetching stored data, and tracking changes to entries.
